fields.title: You will Never Walk Alone
fields.content:
We are the legions of voices in your head,

You will never walk alone!

When you find true religion,

You're gonna find us there,

You will never walk alone!

fields.title: Don't Tell Me No
fields.content:
I'm gonna make it,

Don't tell me no!

I'm forging ahead, yeah,

Aiming for greatness -

And victory is sure;

 

I'm getting double

For all my troubles -

It's my moment,

Yes, I own it,

Don't tell me no; 

 

Don't tell me no!

fields.title: Camouflage
fields.content:
So you've spent all of your days seeking vengeance,

You look so pretty in a camouflage;

You got me where you want me,

Are you gonna shoot me now?

Are you gonna shoot me now?

I'm cool with it, pull the trigger now!

fields.title: The Sun Shall Soon Shine Again
fields.content:
Hey, this is not the end,

What's a storm, I've survived hurricanes!

I don't mind if it pours and I'm drenched to my skin,

Cos I know the sun shall soon shine again.

fields.title: The Dust I leave Behind
fields.content:
Haters in my DM like,

"Knee-guh, what you tryna proove?"

With you're skin so black, You ain't got no swag,

Not even followers on Instagram;

 

I put my hands in the air,

Tell 'em I don't care

Keep on hating all you like!

I am a rocket blasting off, yeah,

Feed on the dust I leave behind.

fields.title: Robots and Dinosaurs
fields.content:
The Spartan Kings rode the Trojan horse,

The regent Queen brought the London bus;

As for me in my adventures,

There'll be robots and dinosaurs.

fields.title: Red Hot Desire
fields.content:
I came, I saw, I conquered,

The men I fought were monsters,

The world is now on fire,

It's burning from my red hot desire.

fields.title: Code Sample
fields.content:
Fishers of Men

This entry is just to check the syntax highlighting capabilites of this blog. I need syntax highlighting to work well because this is going to be a programming tutorial blog. There'll be lots of code blocks. And code blocks are easier read when identifiers are colored appropriately.

So, we start with a function which catcalls a handsome guy.

def hi():
    print("Hello handsome!")

Then, we end with a function which saves face when the handsome guy totally ignores the catcall.

def bye():
    print("Boy bye!")

Which is just right, because like cookie would say:

Ain't nobody want ya sad, angry ass, boy!

Okay, so I'm hoping code highlighting works! Please, let it work, universe... Please!

Edit: It bloody works!

fields.title: Don't Be Ashamed
fields.content:
Don't be ashamed of what you've been through,

Be proud of all the ugly things you've overcome;

Don't be ashamed of what you've been through,

Get loud about the demons you have fought and won -

You have overcome!
